parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lose power assist, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering fault light is illuminated
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel shakes or wobbles
the vehicle is hard to steer
the power steering system fails to assist
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lose power assist, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel shakes or wobbles
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering rack and pinion assembly needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column or Steering Wheel Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column or steering wheel can cause the steering wheel to become loose or detached, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel is loose or wobbly
the steering wheel is not completely secured to the steering column
the steering wheel can be moved from side to side or up and down on the column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or jerk, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The power steering fails to assist
the steering wheel locks or becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear shifter failure can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The gear shifter fails to move or becomes stuck
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the transmission warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical issues
such as faulty warning lights
malfunctioning accessories
or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine coolant leaks can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure, stalling, and potentially catching fire, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Low coolant warning light
overheating
white smoke from the exhaust
engine stalling
loss of power
coolant leaks
and engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents.

jerking
loss of power
stalling
and transmission failure.
